The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
Archives
 Corporate Briefs
																								 Ipca has reported a 24 per cent rise in net income at Rs 300.45 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, 2007, against 242.98 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The net profit rose 28 per cent to Rs 45.42 crore from Rs 35.40 crore in the same period of the previous year. The earnings per share for the quarter stood at Rs 18.05 per share of Rs 10 each. The board has declared an interim dividend of 35 per cent for the financial year 2007-08. 																								 HSBC Private Equity (Asia) Limited and ePlanet will invest $11 million in Trivitron. Both firms will hold a minority stake in Trivitron. The funds will facilitate Trivitrons manufacturing plans through acquisitions and joint ventures and will be used for the infrastructure development of its forthcoming medical technology park. 																								 Kansai Nerolac Paints Ltd has registered a 5.8 per cent rise in gross sales at Rs 425.57 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, 2007, against Rs 402.26 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. The profit before tax rose 8.5 per cent to Rs 47.68 crore from Rs 43.93 crore a year ago.																								 Zicom Electronic Security Systems Ltd has posted a total income of Rs 73.36 crore and a net profit of Rs 3.88 crore for the half year ended September 30, 2007. It reported a total income of Rs 40.52 crore and profit after tax of Rs 1.64 crore for the second quarter ended September 30.																								 The Facor group has reported a 52.38 per cent rise in net sales at Rs 266.05 crore for the second quarter ended September 30, 2007, against Rs 174.60 crore in the year-ago period.The net profit increased 248.05 per cent to Rs 43.75 crore from Rs 12.57 crore in the year-ago period.																								 Kaveri Seed has registered a net profit of Rs 13.74 crore for the half year ended September 30 against Rs 5.96 crore in the corresponding quarter of the previous year. Total income was Rs 72.48 crore compared with Rs 44.95 crore a year ago. ADVERTISEMENT
